  "text": "Finally the use of the backpropagation algorithm in a single hidden layer network might be seen as an efficient shortcut for more plausible learning algorithms operating over deeper, hierarchically organized networks. Critically, the property exhibited by our model to learn identical weights for the same letters at different locations appears not to be limited to backpropagation or to visual words, as it has recently been mirrored on a non-linguistic training base and with the Trace rule, a hebbian learning rule with a temporal window [CITATION_1] .",
